  <p>
    Stylesheets loaded using
    <code>@import</code>
    negatively affect your rendering performance as they are not caught by the
    preload scanner and are a late-discovered resource.
  </p>
  <p>
    In this demo, we are loading
    <code>import.css</code>
    in the document's
    <code>&lt;head&gt;</code>. This stylesheet includes
    <code>@import url(./vars.css);</code>
    â€”where we define our CSS variables.
  </p>
  <p>
    <img
      src="./import.png?v=1668084740368"
      alt="WebPageTest waterfall chart showing four resources. The Start Render mark appears at 3.2s."
    />
  </p>
  <p>
    As you can see in the waterfall chart, the Start Render mark is delayed
    until the render-blocking
    <code>vars.css</code>
    has downloaded.
    Additionally, <code>vars.css</code>
    is downloaded in sequence, after
    <code>import.css</code>
    finishes downloading.
  </p>
